  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600.85 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6605, dealers are likely selling delta into any push higher while providing buying support on dips toward the 6590 negative gamma zone. The PIN regime with massive 41B in total GEX creates a tight trading range between 6590-6620, where dealers will aggressively fade moves away from current levels. The 386% 1-minute GEX surge indicates heavy options flow just hit the market, reinforcing these hedging dynamics and tightening the expected trading range.\n\nKey strikes: 6605 resistance (dealer selling), 6590 support (dealer buying), 6620 flip level above.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy sideways price action pinned between 6590-6620 with dealers fighting any breakout attempts.",
